BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260317T131510Z
DTSTART:20260325T081900Z
DTEND:20260325T082200Z
SUMMARY:Keynote: Keeping Sovereignty on Track: Kubernetes Powering a National Railway Platform - Thomas Comtet\, Senior Staff Engineer\, SNCF & Yann Rotilio\, Senior Staff Engineer - Kubernetes Specialist\, SNCF
DESCRIPTION:As France’s national railway operator\, SNCF has always treated data governance and operational control as mission-critical. That priority became even more urgent when we launched our large-scale cloud migration program in 2018.\n\nToday\, 70% of our 2\,000 applications run across public clouds\, modernized through containers\, serverless architectures\, and managed services. Kubernetes quickly became a central pillar of this transformation and now powers roughly 30% of our application portfolio. At scale—operating more than 200 Kubernetes clusters across Azure and AWS—we learned that Kubernetes is not just a container orchestrator\; it is the control plane for modern application platforms.\n\nBut we also learned something deeper: Kubernetes performs best when it runs on infrastructure that is predictable\, programmable\, and fully under your control. Networking\, storage\, compute\, and load balancing must be designed to serve Kubernetes—not constrain it.\n\nTo bring that level of control to our remaining on premise workloads\, we built our private cloud strategy around Kubernetes and full automation. In 2023\, we selected OpenStack to provide the infrastructure layer beneath it\, enabling us to deliver a cloud-native platform with public-cloud parity while maintaining sovereignty and governance requirements. In addition Openstack allows us to serve simple architectural patterns based on Virtual Machines\, simple solutions for simple needs. \n\nThe overall result is a high-performance\, open-source platform where Kubernetes is the consistent abstraction layer across every environment—public and private—allowing us to continue modernizing applications at scale while retaining full control of our infrastructure's future.
CATEGORIES:KEYNOTE SESSIONS
LOCATION:Hall 12\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:10fcd25ee6ea03a74a94f8ea68471526
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/10fcd25ee6ea03a74a94f8ea68471526
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260317T131510Z
DTSTART:20260325T082400Z
DTEND:20260325T082900Z
SUMMARY:Sponsored Keynote: Inference and Sovereign AI: Scaling Cloud-Native AI with Control and Compliance - Cara Delia\, Manager of AI Community Infrastructure\, Red Hat & Vincent Caldeira\, Chief Technology Officer\, APAC\, Red Hat
DESCRIPTION:AI is moving rapidly from experimentation to critical production workloads—but deploying inference pipelines at scale presents unique challenges. Enterprises need solutions that are high-performance\, resilient\, and compliant\, ensuring both operational efficiency and data sovereignty.\n\nHere we will introduce Sovereign AI\, a Kubernetes-native approach to orchestrating inference workloads that balances performance\, scalability\, and control. We’ll explore real-world strategies for hardware-aware scheduling\, dynamic scaling\, multi-tenant resource management\, and observability\, helping teams run low-latency\, high-throughput AI services on heterogeneous infrastructure. Attendees will learn practical patterns for containerizing models\, optimizing GPU and accelerator usage\, and monitoring AI workloads in production\, all while maintaining compliance with regulatory or enterprise requirements. Harness Kubernetes to deploy AI workloads that are not only efficient and resilient but also secure and sovereign.
CATEGORIES:KEYNOTE SESSIONS
LOCATION:Hall 12\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:12e2789ae56ea60445349a1eb481e7c6
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/12e2789ae56ea60445349a1eb481e7c6
