SUMMARY:Keynote: Powering the European Space Agency’s Space Missions with Open Source Software - Aaron Whitehouse\, Senior Product Manager\, Canonical
DESCRIPTION:You can’t explore space without infrastructure. It’s not just expert personnel\, satellites\, and spacecraft: it takes mountains of software\, computer systems\, data and networks to get space &nbsp\;missions off the ground. To meet its objective of doubling the number of space missions by 2030\, ESA started work on a solution that would allow it to deploy infrastructure and software automatically for its missions\, and simplify the workflow and processes for ESA engineering teams. The agency enlisted Canonical’s help in building and managing an open source infrastructure stack that would launch its missions into the future. This talk will take the audience on a journey into space\, showing how open source software can help reach new frontiers.
CATEGORIES:KEYNOTE SESSIONS
LOCATION:Hall 12\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:3434c8f092bab4ed7e5f3c565916b012
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/3434c8f092bab4ed7e5f3c565916b012
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260317T131510Z
DTSTART:20260325T084100Z
DTEND:20260325T084600Z
SUMMARY:Sponsored Keynote: From Pilot to Production: Scaling and Optimizing Agentic Workloads on Kubernetes - Idit Levine\, Founder & CEO\, Solo.io & Keith Babo\, Chief Product Officer\, Solo.io
DESCRIPTION:Kubernetes and the CNCF ecosystem are rapidly evolving to support agent-native workloads\, with open-source projects like agentgateway and kagent extending Kubernetes to treat agents\, tools\, and skills as first-class citizens. With this foundation in place\, platform teams can bring agentic workloads to production. But getting to production is just the beginning. The real challenge is what happens when you scale - moving beyond a few specialized teams getting initial projects to production to every developer in your organization integrating with agents\, tools\, and skills as part of their core workflow.\n\nThis talk will cover the concrete infrastructure patterns emerging in the community for discovery\, governance\, and operational excellence as agentic workloads move from pilot to enterprise scale.\n\n
CATEGORIES:KEYNOTE SESSIONS
LOCATION:Hall 12\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:8a870483f2da5b962d9ed83226bd1114
