BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260317T131510Z
DTSTART:20260325T100000Z
DTEND:20260325T103000Z
SUMMARY:Lima Project Updates: Expanding the Focus To Hardening AI - Akihiro Suda\, NTT & Anshuman Sahoo\, BITS Pilani
DESCRIPTION:Lima (Linux Machines) is a command line tool to launch a local Linux virtual machine\, with the primary focus on running containers on a laptop.\n\nAside from container workloads\, Lima is also known to be useful for running an AI coding agent inside a VM. This setup ensures that even if an AI agent is deceived by malicious instructions searched from the Internet (e.g.\, fake package installations)\, any potential damage is confined within the VM or limited to files specified to be mounted from the host.\n\nIn this session\, the maintainers will introduce the recent news in the project\, including:\n- Promotion to CNCF Incubating (October 2025)\n- New features in v2.0 (November 2025)\n- Plugin infrastructure\n- GPU acceleration\n- MCP server\n- Other updates planned in v2.1 and onward.\n\nProject website: https://lima-vm.io/
CATEGORIES:MAINTAINER TRACK
LOCATION:Amtrium 1+2\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:4831a94bdf5398a4e7d6f8c5db20a007
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/4831a94bdf5398a4e7d6f8c5db20a007
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260317T131510Z
DTSTART:20260325T100000Z
DTEND:20260325T103000Z
SUMMARY:Linkerd: Reliable Production in an AI/MCP World - William Morgan\, Buoyant
DESCRIPTION:Linkerd is evolving. In this talk\, we’ll share how the Linkerd maintainers are partnering with organizations that are pushing the boundaries of cloud native\, through scale\, sophistication\, or through the deployment of a new class of workloads: LLMs\, agentic AI workloads\, and MCP servers. By learning from real-world incidents—sometimes triggered by Linkerd\, more often revealed by it—we’re reshaping the project’s roadmap to become an even more powerful reliability layer for platform teams. \n \n We’ll discuss lessons learned\, features delivered\, and the upcoming roadmap for Linkerd designed to help platform engineers stabilize failing infrastructure\, isolate app issues\, and move forward with confidence\, even in AI and MCP environments. You’ll get a behind-the-scenes look at the upcoming 2.20 release and how production lessons are being directly applied to build a system that thrives under pressure.
CATEGORIES:MAINTAINER TRACK
LOCATION:E103-105\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:25a7b5f59ffd4f0bede33f46f448aec1
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/25a7b5f59ffd4f0bede33f46f448aec1
