END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260317T131510Z
DTSTART:20260325T100000Z
DTEND:20260325T103000Z
SUMMARY:Strengthening CNCF Projects: Impact of Security Self-Assessments - Eddie Knight\, Sonatype; Bradley Andersen\, k8gb; Justin Cappos\, New York University; Shuting Zhao\, Nirmata; Orlin Vasilev\, SUSE
DESCRIPTION:This panel brings together TAG Security and Compliance Technical Leads and maintainers who have completed TAG Security and Compliance self-assessments to discuss how this process transformed their security posture. From identifying blind spots to implementing best practices\, panelists will share practical insights on navigating the assessment\, addressing findings\, and building security into their projects' DNA. \n \n Attendees will learn: \n - How the self-assessment process works and why it matters for CNCF projects \n - Real-world challenges and wins from projects that completed assessments \n - Actionable security improvements that emerged from the process \n - How to approach security documentation and threat modeling \n - Tips for maintainers considering or starting their own assessment \n \n Whether you're a maintainer preparing for an assessment or curious about elevating your project's security practices\, this panel offers practical guidance from those who've been through the journey.
CATEGORIES:MAINTAINER TRACK
LOCATION:G102-103\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:b5acab59190918cbdca3ba021e40cffb
