SUMMARY:Sponsored Demo: KubeHound: Identifying Attack Paths in Kubernetes Clusters at Scale
DESCRIPTION:KubeHound is an open source tool developed by Datadog that discovers attack paths in Kubernetes clusters. Security scanners give you lists: 14 container escapes\, 32 privilege escalations\, 72 lateral movements. But a list cannot answer the question that matters most: which of those findings can be used to access critical assets in your cluster? KubeHound takes a different approach. Instead of treating each finding as an isolated problem\, KubeHound builds a graph showing how misconfigurations—like an over-privileged service account or a hostPath mount—chain together into exploitable attack paths. This is how an attacker sees your cluster: not as a list of problems\, but as a map of opportunities. The speaker will live demo how KubeHound works\, connecting common misconfigurations to industry-standard MITRE ATT&CK techniques\, and chaining those attacks together. Attendees will leave ready to run KubeHound on their own clusters—the same tool used by security teams across Datadog. **In order to facilitate networking and business relationships at the event\, you may choose to visit a third party’s booth or access sponsored content. You are never required to visit third party booths or to access sponsored content. When visiting a booth or participating in sponsored activities\, the third party will receive some of your registration data. This data includes your first name\, last name\, title\, company\, address\, email\, standard demographics questions (i.e. job function\, industry)\, and details about the sponsored content or resources you interacted with. If you choose to interact with a booth or access sponsored content\, you are explicitly consenting to receipt and use of such data by the third-party recipients\, which will be subject to their own privacy policies.**
